records.nl_statement: Suppose (a) $f$ is continuous for $x \geq 0$, (b) $f^{\prime}(x)$ exists for $x>0$, (c) $f(0)=0$, (d) $f^{\prime}$ is monotonically increasing. Put $g(x)=\frac{f(x)}{x} \quad(x>0)$ and prove that $g$ is monotonically increasing.
